result.execSummary:
This case has not been concluded. Unless a judgment of conviction is entered, the defendant is presumed innocent of all charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
9:26 AM Defendant Trevor Joseph Sanigar in court, in custody.  Attorney Ryan Anthony Reid in court for Trevor Joseph Sanigar.  Attorney Allison E. Cogbill in court for State of Wisconsin. Court calls case. Attorney states their client wishes to waive their right to the preliminary hearing. Defendant agrees. Court accepts waiver of the Defendant's right to a preliminary hearing as knowingly and voluntarily made. Court finds probable cause and binds the defendant over for arraignment. Court reminds the Defendant of their bail conditions. Defendant orally confirms he has received date and time of hearing and confirms he will attend. Defendant provided notice.
Arraignment scheduled for November 21, 2022 at 10:30 am.
Defendant's Demand for Discovery and Inspection
records.descr: Demand for Discovery and Inspection - Defendant

records.addlTxt:
3:34 PM Defendant Trevor Joseph Sanigar appeared by video, in custody.  Attorney Ryan Anthony Reid in court for Trevor Joseph Sanigar.  Prosecuting attorney Allison E. Cogbill in court for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant's address confirmed. Attorney/Defendant acknowledges receipt of the complaint, waives a formal reading, and requests a preliminary hearing. State asks for $2000 cash. No special conditions. State notes nature of offense and 8 prior FTAs. Notes prior convictions including 2 failure to report jail convictions. State recites prior cash bails posted. Attorney Reid notes that defendant is lifelong resident of the county with family and contacts to the community. Asks for up to $1000 cash.
Court notes concerns over the nature of charges, recent FTAs and failure to report to jail convictions
Court orders $2000 cash bail. No special conditions.
Preliminary hearing scheduled for October 12, 2022 at 09:30 am.
